  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    DiscardObjectAfterInvocation
    Indicates that the object with this method, or a certain parameter, should be discarded after invoking this method.
    ExpectedFailureProfile
    Communicates the failure mode of annotated class/method.
    ExpectedPerformanceProfile
    Communicates the expected performance characteristic to the programmer using the class.
    HasSideEffects
    Indicates that the method/type/field has some side effects.
    MayModify
    Indicates that the parameter will be mutated in some way.
    OwnershipTransferredToTarget
    Parameter object annotated by this value will have its lifecycle managed by invoked method.
    ReadOnly
    This annotation attempts to communicate to other API users that the value produced by the method or passed as a parameter should be only read from.
    Reentrancy
    Indicates whether this method can be invoked again before other invocations are complete OR whether this method can be executed only once in object's lifetime.
    RefactorThis
    Indicates that the following piece of code should be refactored.
